Three young children, aged between 6 and 9 have drowned in Reefentse, north of Pretoria. Courtesy #DStv403 PRETORIA - Three young children, aged between 6 and 9, have drowned in Reefentse, north of Pretoria. Tshwane EMS Spokesperson Charles Mabaso says the three boys drowned at a waterlogged park. "The bodies of two boys were recovered by community members. Emergency services recovered the body of the third boy." Mabaso says the park was waterlogged due to the recent rains. Watch the full interview with Tshwane EMS Spokesperson Charles Mabaso above.